<br>
Name has been determined, but will be withheld for the time being.<br>
<br>
This is to be a RP heavy EVIL only guild, however what I feel will set us apart is this:<br>
<br>
    Who defines what is evil?  Usually those in power. <br>
    There was a time when Native Americans were<br>
    thought of as evil by citizens of the United States, the<br>
    Zulu warriors where considered evil by the British<br>
    Empire, Jews and Muslims were considered evil by<br>
    the Roman Catholic Church ( I am speaking<br>
    historically in all these cases and do not wish to turn<br>
    this into a rant on current events).  Look at the map of<br>
    Norath and see who controls the land.  It is any<br>
    surprise we are branded evil?<br>
<br>
    Our ways are not understood by those who call<br>
    themselves &quot;good&quot;. They raid our lands and murder<br>
    our soldiers, their guards wander the land and slay us<br>
    on sight.  They send massive raids against our cities<br>
    and the cities of our kin, killing even the merchants<br>
    and barmaids.  And yet we are evil.<br>
<br>
That is the basis for what I shall refer to as Our Guild or simply the Guild.  We are players from evil races who do not see ourselves as evil.<br>
<br>
The Guild will be mostly, but not exclusively Dark Elf.  Ogres, Trolls, Humans, Gnomes and anyone who can walk unmolested in Neriak ( at least the foreign quarter ).  Alignment must be evil.  Races NOT allowed are Iksar ( they are KOS in our cities, we are KOS in theirs ), High Elf, Wood Elf, Barbarians, Vah Shir, Dwarves, Halflings.  Alignments of Good or Neutral are not allowed.<br>
<br>
Our Guild is to be a Democracy of sorts.  Leadership will be made up of a circle of five officers, with ten advisors below them ( this number is to be filled gradually as the guild grows and will not be on a first come first severed basis.  The officers will vote on any important matters winning with a simple majority.  Should the matter end in a tie ( due to absence or abstaining ) those advisors in attendance will be brought in to vote.  Should the matter still end in a tie the matter will be set aside and voted on by all members, posted out of game with one week to vote.  I would be the first officer, and pick the other four based on merit.  The ten advisors will also be based on merit, and the officers will vote on each.<br>
<br>
Initially there will be not level requirement for joining, but this will eventually be changed first to level 10 and then 15, exceptions may be made for needed classes ( Clerics for one ).<br>
<br>
And in general we will follow the practices set up and deemed fair by the majority of guilds on this server.<br>
<br>
If you've read this much you must be at least marginally interested.  Reply to this proposal with contact information if you would like to know more and I will either contact you in game (leave name and times you are usually on) or by email.<br>
<br>
